# Dependencies must be local (no global installs)

- Do **not** install this project’s required dependencies globally (system Python, user site-packages, global pip, etc.).
- Install and run dependencies from a **local virtual environment** inside the repo (prefer `.venv`).

## Required behavior

- If a venv is missing, create it locally (prefer `uv venv`).
- Install/sync dependencies into the local venv (prefer `uv sync`).
- Run project commands using the local environment (prefer `uv run ...`).

## Avoid

- `pip install ...` outside a venv
- `pip install --user ...`
- Modifying global Python environments to “make it work”

